frameDefinitions: Words in this frame describe acts in violation of a legal code.

The words in this frame describe situations in which a Perpetrator forcibly seizes control over a Victim's Vehicle to gain some end.  '' 'French farmers have hijacked a lorry and destroyed its load of strawberries.'
A Perpetrator (generally intentionally) commits a Crime, i.e. does something not permitted by the laws of society.
A Helper benefits a Benefited_party by enabling the culmination of a Goal that the Benefited_party has.
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
A Wrongdoer engages in a Misdeed.
frameExamples: He was accused of <t><fex name='Offense'>hijacking</fex></t> a tour bus full of people.
French farmers have <t>hijacked</t> a lorry and destroyed its load of strawberries.
They <t>perpetrated</t> a felony by substituting a lie for negotiations.
Will you <t>help</t> the Government find your brother?
As soon as he stepped out of the bar he was <t>set</t> upon by four men in ski-masks.
You have <t>sinned</t> for the last time, Stephen!
listRoleDefinitions: The illegal act.
This role denotes the person or entity that is badly affected by the <fen>Offense</fen>.
The individual who commits the Offense
This is the person (or other agent) who forcibly seizes control over a vehicle to gain some end.
This is the means of transportation which gets under the control of the perpetrator. Example: The terrorists hijacked <fex name='Vehicle'>the plane</fex>.
This role describes the people that are suffering as a result of the <fen>Perpetrator</fen>'s action.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The individual that commits a <fen>Crime</fen>.
An act, generally intentional, that has been formally forbidden by law.
When the <fen>Crime</fen> was committed.
The location where the <fen>Crime</fen> occurs.
The <fen>Benefited_party</fen> receives a benefit from the action of the <fen>Helper</fen>.
The <fen>Helper</fen> performs some action that benefits the <fen>Benefited_party</fen>.
The desirable state of affairs that the <fen>Benefited_party</fen> is involved in and which is enabled by the <fen>Helper</fen>.
This role identifies a <fen>Focal_entity</fen> involved in achieving the <fen>Goal</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the Assistance occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the Assistance occurs.
This role is the being or entity that is injured by the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Assailant</fen> attacks the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Assailant</fen> makes an assault on the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This is the person whose <fen>Misdeed</fen> is being judged with respect to its morality.
The assessment of the <fen>Wrongdoer</fen> is based on his or her <fen>Misdeed</fen>.
The time at which a <fen>Misdeed</fen> is performed.
The location where a <fen>Misdeed</fen> occurs.

The police assisted Harry in finding his cat <fex>in front of his house</fex>.

<fex>The mysterious fighter</fex> attacked the guardsmen with a sabre.
